   <descr>
      <p>"Separate Lives" is a 1985 song recorded by Phil Collins and
    Marilyn Martin and featured on the soundtrack to the motion
    picture 
    <i>White Nights</i>. It reached #1 on the Billboard Hot 100
    chart and #4 on the UK Singles Chart. The song also topped the
    adult contemporary chart in the U.S. for three weeks.</p>
      <p>Songwriter Stephen Bishop received an Oscar nomination for
    Best Original Song. It lost to Lionel Richie's "Say You, Say
    Me" from the same movie.</p>
